==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sophism
<hw>Soph"ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>sophisme</ets>, L. <ets>sophisma</ets>, fr. Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to
make wise, <?/ to be become wise, to play the sophist, fr. <?/
wise.]</ety> <def>The doctrine or mode of reasoning practiced by a
sophist; hence, any fallacy designed to deceive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When a false argument puts on the appearance of a true one, then
it is properly called a <qex>sophism</qex>, or
⟦ldquo⟧fallacy⟦rdquo⟧.</q> <rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let us first rid ourselves of <qex>sophisms</qex>, those of
depraved men, and those of heartless philosophers.</q> <rj><qau>I.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sophist</ent>⟦br⟧
